Program: Omnibus
Title: Global Perspective - The Island on Dry Land
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376m54
Last Broadcast Date: 08 February 2001
Profile of what happened to the island of Schokland, which used to be in the Zuyderzee, Schokland lost its status as an island when the Noordoostpolder was reclaimed from the sea in 1942. Presenter: Michele Ernsting